==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: clubmoss
<hw>clubmoss</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>a primitive evergreen mosslike plant with spores
in club-shaped strobiles, much used in winter decoration. The best known
species is <spn>Lycopodium clavatum</spn>, but other
<gen>Lycopodia</gen> are often called by this name. The spores form a
highly inflammable powder.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> club moss, lycopod.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clubbed</ent>⟦br⟧
